Build a control execution screen for "CM-04: Segregation of Developer Access Between DEV and PRD" 
inside the existing SAP ITGC Audit Tool (GAD IT). Match the existing app's shell: top nav tabs 
(Change Management / Access Controls / IT Operations), password-gated entry, and the "Audit Trail & 
Accountability" pattern already used by other controls (auditor name field logged with every run, 
per-control export button, automatic audit trail download).

CONTROL OBJECTIVE
Ensure users with developer access in the Development (DEV) environment do not also have equivalent 
developer access in the Production (PRD) environment.

CARD LAYOUT (top to bottom)
1. Header: "CM-04: Segregation of Developer Access – DEV vs PRD"
2. Objective text (one line, from above)
3. Audit steps (numbered, static text):
   1. Run SUIM (or the relevant authorization object/T-code) and generate developer access lists 
      separately for DEV and PRD.
   2. Upload both extracts below.
   3. Enter the audit period (From Month / To Month).
   4. The tool filters user types, checks active validity, and compares the two lists automatically.
   5. Users appearing as active developers in both DEV and PRD are flagged as exceptions.

4. AUDIT PERIOD PARAMETERS (required before Run is enabled)
   - "From Month" — month/year picker (e.g. Apr 2025)
   - "To Month" — month/year picker (e.g. Jun 2026)
   - Helper text (info style, see colors below): "Defines the applicable audit period, including 
     prior FY carry-forward and current FY YTD. Used to test whether each user's Valid To date 
     falls within/after this window."
   - Validation: To Month must be >= From Month.

5. TWO FILE UPLOAD FIELDS (side by side or stacked)
   - Upload field A: "DEV Developer Access Extract" — accepts .csv, .xlsx, .xls
   - Upload field B: "PRD Developer Access Extract" — accepts .csv, .xlsx, .xls
   - Each upload shows filename once selected, plus a "Mandatory Columns" info panel:
       • BNAME / USERNAME – User ID
       • USER TYPE – must be A (Dialog) or S (System); other types are filtered out
       • VALID FROM – access start date
       • VALID TO – access end date (blank = still active)
       • Optional: LOCK STATUS, ROLE / AUTH OBJECT (developer access indicator, e.g. S_DEVELOP / SE38 / SE80)
     Note under panel: "Column order does not matter. Ensure the dump contains these fields; 
     auditors should preserve original SAP/client headers wherever possible."
   - Parsing logic:
       • .csv → parse as delimited text.
       • .xlsx/.xls → parse the first worksheet as a table (header row + data rows); ignore 
         additional sheets.
       • Normalize both into the same internal row structure before running validation logic — 
         comparison logic must be format-agnostic.
   - Flexible column matching (case-insensitive, tolerate header variants like 'User Name' vs 
     'BNAME' vs 'Username'), applied identically regardless of source format.
   - Unsupported file type → inline error: "Unsupported file type. Please upload a .csv, .xlsx, 
     or .xls file."

6. "Run CM-04 Test" button (disabled until both files are uploaded and both months are selected)

7. VALIDATION LOGIC (implement exactly, in this order)
   a. Parse both uploaded files into DEV list and PRD list.
   b. Filter Users: retain only rows where USER TYPE is 'A' or 'S' (case-insensitive); drop all others.
   c. Validate Active Access: for each remaining row, keep it only if:
        - VALID TO is blank/null, OR
        - VALID TO falls within [From Month start date, To Month end date] inclusive, OR
        - VALID TO is after To Month end date (still active through the audit period)
      i.e. exclude only users whose access clearly expired before the audit period's From Month.
   d. Compare Lists: take filtered/active DEV usernames and filtered/active PRD usernames; compute 
      the intersection (case-insensitive match on username/BNAME; normalize to uppercase first).
   e. Any username present in both active lists is an EXCEPTION.
   f. Dedupe: if a username appears multiple times in one file (e.g. multiple roles), count it once 
      per environment.

8. OUTPUT AREA (after Run)
   - Summary strip: "Users Reviewed (DEV): X | Users Reviewed (PRD): Y | Active Developers (DEV): A 
     | Active Developers (PRD): B | Exceptions Found: N"
   - Result chip/banner:
       • PASS chip (green) — "CM-04 executed successfully — No common active developer users found 
         between DEV and PRD" if N = 0
       • FAIL chip (red) — "CM-04 executed — N exception(s) identified" if N > 0
   - Exceptions table (only rendered if N > 0), columns:
       USERNAME | USER TYPE (DEV) | VALID TO (DEV) | USER TYPE (PRD) | VALID TO (PRD) | STATUS = "Exception"
   - Missing mandatory column in either file → warning banner above results: "One or more mandatory 
     columns are missing in [DEV/PRD] extract: <list>" — block execution until resolved.

9. AUDIT TRAIL LOGGING (on every run, success or exception)
   Log: Control ID (CM-04), Control Name, Auditor/User Name (existing global field), Run timestamp, 
   DEV file name, PRD file name, From Month, To Month, Users Reviewed (DEV/PRD), Active Developers 
   (DEV/PRD), Exceptions Found, and the exception list itself.

10. EXPORT
    - "Export CM-04 Audit Trail (Excel/CSV)" — same pattern as other controls (auto-downloads).
    - Includes: run metadata (auditor, timestamp, audit period), full exception table, counts summary.

EDGE CASES
- Empty file upload → inline error, don't crash.
- Username casing mismatches → normalize to uppercase before comparing.
- Duplicate rows for same user in one file → dedupe before building active list.
- USER TYPE column missing entirely → validation error, not silent skip.

